FBIS4-63915 "drsov102_b_94016" FBIS-SOV-94-102 Daily Report 25 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Space Issues Defense Spokesman: Troop Unrest if Budget Not Increased Defense Spokesman: Troop Unrest if Budget Not Increased LD2505205294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1830 GMT 25 May 94 LD2505205294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Russian BFN [Text] Major General Vladimir Osadchiy, a key figure in the Main Military Budget and Financing Directorate of Russia's Defence Ministry, said that the social aspect has become decisive in the reform of Russia's armed forces. Osadchiy believes that if the military budget is implemented in its present form then half of all servicemen will not be able to receive their pay within the term set by law. Two to three months without pay would lead inevitably lead to a worsening of the already difficult situation among the troops.
